summary: This appears to be an FBI email or intake log summarizing the receipt of multiple anonymous tips and information submissions related to the Epstein case between July 2020 and December 2020. The document lists various dates, times, and file attachments for each submission, indicating ongoing public interest and information flow to law enforcement.

keyFacts: The FBI received a continuous stream of tips and information related to the Epstein case from July through December 2020.
Multiple submissions were made by anonymous tipsters, including at least one anonymous female caller.
The document references an interview (EFTA00080615) that appears to be a follow-up to this intake log.
The file attachments suggest submissions included documents with dates of birth, email addresses, and phone numbers.
The document indicates ongoing public engagement with law enforcement regarding the Epstein investigation well after his death.
